SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 677
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Kendall Warner on receiving the
Nursing Faculty Clinical Excellence Award from
Walters State Community College.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pay tribute to
those medical professionals who have wholly devoted themselves to serving others and thereby
contribute significantly to the well-being of their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, Kendall Warner of Mohawk is one such exceptional medical professional,
who recently received the Nursing Faculty Clinical Excellence Award from Walters State
Community College (WSCC), an honor most befitting what has been an auspicious start to her
career in nursing; and
WHEREAS, winners of the Nursing Excellence Awards are nominated by their
managers, peers, and other team members and chosen based on their dedication, exceptional
clinical practice, outcomes, and distinguished contributions to the nursing profession; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Warner received the award during WSCC's Nursing Pinning Ceremony
for fall semester graduates; and
WHEREAS, Kendall Warner is a leader in her profession, and her devotion to providing
quality, compassionate care to her patients is most worthy of our approbation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we commend and honor Kendall Warner upon her
receipt of the Nursing Faculty Clinical Excellence Award and extend to her our best wishes for a
happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
